            <scopecontent id="aspace_b8b6241657c6927442ff1f77c47db5cb">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Lined notebook, 15.5 x 10 cm,  with pages folded on the bottom that extend to 20.5 cm. The first pages contain a narrative that begins January 3, 1945 with Oughterson's departure from the Unites States and his arrival in Japan. He describes bombs and air raids. Other parts of the notebook, most of which is blank, contain miscellaneous notes. The folder also includes a separate sheet of paper containing references from 1942 to 1947, and a larger sheet on which Oughterson has written, "This is a bone fida gift from a member of the Armed Forces and entitled to free entry."</p>
            </scopecontent>
         </c>
